		<div id="comment_body_64649176"><p>I think Amazon made the problem much worse by delivering a poor developer experience.  I'm an experienced enterprise developer, and I spent a weekend trying to<br>develop a skill using the Alexa API (I think it was called "Alex").  I wasn't developing a complicated skill - it was nothing more than a "hello world" type of effort.  I couldn't get it to work.  The documentation was confusing.  The support channels were minimal.</p><p>3rd-party developers (like me) could have elevated this smart-timer to a multi-skilled market dominator given the right support.  There are a lot of cool things developers can build on AWS with a connection to an interactive speech-to-text device - and that may have turned around the fortunes of this overpriced 555 timer.</p></div>
